TO DO:
======

- Reorganize directory structure.

- Clean up C external code.

- Further review of figures cluster.
  (Feature names like `angle_rel_to' are a bad smell.)


TO FIX/INVESTIGATE/COMPLETE:
===========================

- Text editor capture behaves differently from diagram tool capture in bench.

- Check consistency of show_modal enable/disable modal features.
  Define explicit behavior for modal windows/dialogs and test both platforms.

- Postscript projector and print dialogs to be completed.

- Pixmap saving to be completed, includes fixing alpha support in EV_COLOR.
  (Potentially hard on both platforms)

- Pixmap loading needs to be revised so that load_from_buffer and load_from_file
  work the same way. (GEL implementor should check progress of GdkPixbuf on the
  GTK mailing list)
  (Potentially hard on both platforms)

- Implement pixmap is_equal (awaiting on agent comparison functionality in base).

- EV_RELATIVE_POINT.notify_of_position_change: Remove object_id from list

- Stock cursors and pixmaps to be designed and stored in eiffel files.
  (Base64 encoding should be put into base library and used for this)

- EV_COLOR.delta: test on different platforms/color depths/system loads.

- EV_COLOR alpha channel integration (2d -IK)

- (GEL) Tooltips only displayed on lowest widget in a vertical box of widgets.

- (GEL) Tree: After minimizing trees stop working in bench. GtkCritical errors.

- (GEL) Make sure selected item in a list (and mc-list) is always visible. 

- (WEL) Implement PND for combo-box and menu. (Fairly difficult - JR)

- (WEL) Implement tooltips on trees. (Quite hard. - JR)

- (WEL) Some destruction order problems (no_calls_after_destroy invariant)

TO ADD:
=======

- EV_FIGURE_WIDGET
  An EV_FIGURE that has features `set_widget (a_widget: EV_WIDGET)',
  `widget: EV_WIDGET' and `remove_widget'. The projector should draw the
  widget at with the upper left corner at the (x,y) position of the figure
  and with the widget's minimum (width, height).
  The best implementation seems to be this: The projector will have an
  EV_FIXED with an EV_DRAWABLE in it. Normal figures will be drawn into the
  drawable as usual. EV_FIGURE_WIDGETs will be placed in the appropriate
  places in the EV_FIXED so as to appear over the normally drawn figures.
  This will mean that the widgets will always obscure other figures but that
  is something we can live with (it is not important to the customer who needs
  this feature)


TO TEST:
========

- PND on all widgets and items

- Tooltips on all tooltipable classes.


