NON RELEASE CRITICAL ITEMS
================================================================================

TO DO:
======

- Speed optimization.

- Resource usage optimization.

- Brainstorm new action sequences.
  parented_actions? displayed_actions?....

- Further review of dialog behaviour.


TO FIX/INVESTIGATE/COMPLETE:
===========================

- ev_font.e Fonts need to be reviewed WRT addition of convenience features
  Points functionality needs to be added to interface (2d - IK)

- Fix broken EV_FIGURE_MATH `distance_from_line' and `point_on_segment' (2d - IK)

- Implement EV_FIGURE `intersects' (3h - IK)

- Implement EV_FIGURE_ARC, EV_FIGURE_PIE_SLICE, EV_FIGURE_POLYLINE,
  EV_FIGURE_RECTANGLE, EV_FIGURE_TEXT `position_on_figure' (3d - IK)

- Implement EV_RELATIVE_POINT `angle_rel_to' (4h - IK)

- Make filters in file dialog more flexible. (Combo box of filters)

- Find a nice way to display a wait cursor and ignore input while processing.

- Small windows in bench (eg class selection window) have inconsistent resizing
  behavior across platforms.

- Add destroy_actions in EV_WIDGET and make sure it works for all descendants.

- EV_DIALOG PR:2231 Dialogs need to have a minimum size so we can control the
  appearance. We need to have control of the size that is not totally
  dependent on the amount of text in the message. - Keith Soper

- Check places that have is_equal in postcondition, mabey add "and /=".

- (WEL) Implement EV_ALIGNMENT.

- (WEL) Implement features like changing title/position for dialogs:
        color font open save directory.

- (WEL) EV_TEXT_IMP  Selecting text using shift and page down. When
        reaching the last page, the cursor is not moved to the last position
		of the text. May be tricky but should not be too hard. - JR

- (WEL) EV_COMBO_BOX_IMP One fixme on internal_propagate_pointer_press which
        I believe stops the pick and drop and possibly the items from
		receiving mouse events properly. -JR

- (WEL) EV_INPUT_DEVICE_DIALOG to open control panel for whatever funky input
        device is installed (it graphics tablet, CAD puck...)

- (WEL) EV_MENU_IMP - One fixme saying that either the text or the pixmap can
        be displayed although not both at the same time which is the desired
		behavior. I would think this is a difficult problem to solve without
		drawing the menu ourselves, which we definitely do not want to do. - JR

- (GEL) EV_WINDOW, Can postcondition of minimize/restore be implemented?

- (GEL) EV_WINDOW, Should set size features be requests since they are
        implemented through WM hints?


